President Obama has nominated Leslie Joyce Abrams to serve on the United States District Court for the Middle District of Georgia. Abrams has had a distinguished legal career, serving as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Northern District of Georgia since 2010. She has also worked at Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher, and Flom LLP and Kilpatrick Stockton LLP. Abrams started her legal career as a law clerk for Judge Marvin J. Garbis of the United States District Court for the District of Maryland. She holds a J.D. from Yale Law School and a B.A. from Brown University. President Obama expressed confidence that Abrams will serve the American people with integrity and a strong commitment to justice.